*'''Expert Combatant''': [[File:Avengers Age of Ultron 32.png|thumb|250px|Quicksilver attacking [[Ultron]]]] Maximoff was an expert at using his powers in combat, defeating several [[Ultron Sentries]], landing an efficient punch against [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]]. His speed allowed him to use it in various ways in combat that nobody else could be able to do. For example, he uses his speed to push into the enemy or graze them so that the force pushes them far. He used this against [[Ultron]] in order to push him out of the way.
*'''Bilingualism''': Maximoff was fluent in his native Sokovian, as well as English, albeit with a heavy Sokovian accent.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''{{WPS|RPK}}''': [[File:NXmN2mVb3U8-1-.jpg|thumb|250px|Quicksilver motivating the police officers]] Maximoff rushed into the Sokovian police station and demanded they clear [[Novi Grad]] for the incoming threat of [[Ultron]]. They ignored him and Maximoff returned with an RPK light machine gun. Maximoff frightened them into action by firing the RPK light machine gun into the roof of their police station.

===Other Equipment===
*'''Uniform''': In preparation for the [[Battle of Sokovia]], Pietro picked out a uniform he found in [[Avengers Tower]] and wore it into battle.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Maximoff Residence]]''': In his childhood, Pietro resided with his parents and sister, [[Wanda Maximoff|Wanda]]. The two twins often watched American television shows to practice their English. One night, they were watching {{WPS|The Dick Van Dyke Show}} when a [[Stark Industries]] bomb landed in their house, killing his parents. A second one then hit, but didn't go off. The twins waited for two days for the bomb to go off until they were finally rescued.
*'''[[Hydra Research Base]]''': During the experiments with the [[Scepter]], Maximoff was living in a [[Hydra]] base. Being specifically as a test subject, Maximoff was held in a room where he trained his powers.

