==Trivia==
*In the comics, Pietro Maximoff is a founding member of the [[w:c:marvel:Brotherhood of Mutants|Brotherhood of Mutants]], being initially identified as the son of [[Magneto]] (Erik Lehnsherr) and his then-wife Magda Lehnsherr (née Eisenhardt) in [[w:c:marvel:Vision and the Scarlet Witch Vol 1 4|''Vision and the Scarlet Witch'' #4]] (1983), nineteen years after [[Scarlet Witch]] and Quicksilver's first appearance. Magda left Erik while pregnant and took sanctuary at [[Mount Wundagore]] in [[Transia Corporation|Transia]], the home of the [[High Evolutionary]], where she gave birth and later died. The High Evolutionary then placed them instead in the care of the {{WPS|Romani}} couple, [[Olek Maximoff|Django]] and [[Iryna Maximoff|Marya Maximoff]], who raised them as their own children. Prior to that, in [[w:c:marvel:Giant-Size Avengers Vol 1 1|''Giant-Size Avengers'' #1]] (1974), they were revealed to be the biological children of Golden Age superheroes The [[Whizzer]] and [[w:c:marvel:Madeline Joyce (Earth-616)|Miss America]], a fact that was later retconned. In [[w:c:marvel:Avengers & X-Men: AXIS Vol 1 7|''Avengers &amp; X-Men: AXIS'' #7]] (2014), it was revealed that Pietro and his sister have no blood ties to Magneto and are not related after all. In [[w:c:marvel:Uncanny Avengers Vol 1 4|''Uncanny Avengers'' #4]] (2015), it is confirmed not only they are not related to Magneto but they are not even [[mutants]], as the High Evolutionary genetically altered them as infants, giving them their powers, before returning them to their true parents, the Maximoffs.<ref name="No Longer Mutants">[http://www.bleedingcool.com/2015/05/07/no-longer-mutants-the-real-father-of-scarlet-witch-and-quicksilver-is/ No Longer Mutants. The Real Parents Of Scarlet Witch And Quicksilver Are...]</ref>
*Pietro states that he is twelve minutes older than [[Wanda Maximoff|Wanda]].
*Pietro's first and final words in ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'' were "You didn't see that coming?," who said it both times to [[Hawkeye]].
*Quicksilver was the first member of the [[Avengers]] to die.

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Quicksilver/Earth-10005|Another version of Quicksilver]] appeared in {{WPS|20th Century Fox}}'s productions ''{{WPS|X-Men: Days of Future Past}}'', ''{{WPS|X-Men: Apocalypse}}'', ''{{WPS|Deadpool 2}}'' and ''{{WPS|Dark Phoenix (film)|Dark Phoenix}}''. He is portrayed by [[Aaron Taylor-Johnson]]'s ''{{WPS|Kick-Ass (film)|Kick-Ass}}'' co-star [[Evan Peters]]. That version is known as "Peter Maximoff," instead of "Pietro;" additionally, the MCU version could not be identified as a mutant. This is due to both Fox and Marvel owning Quicksilver's movie rights, as Quicksilver was heavily involved in both the ''Avengers'' and ''[[X-Men]]'' comics, although Fox owned the rights to all [[Marvel Comics (publisher)|Marvel Comics]] [[Mutants|mutants]] (before the acquisition of 20th Century Fox by [[Walt Disney Studios]]).
**In the Russian dub of ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'', [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] refers to the Maximoff twins as "mutants," instead of "the enhanced."
*[[Aaron Taylor-Johnson]] was uncredited for his appearance in ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]''.
*According to [[James Gunn]], the [[List of Post-credits Scenes|post-credits scene]] from ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]'' featuring Quicksilver and [[Wanda Maximoff]] was originally meant for ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy (film)|Guardians of the Galaxy]]''.<ref>[https://comicbookmovie.com/guardians-of-the-galaxy/guardians-of-the-galaxy-was-supposed-to-have-the-quicksilver-and-scarlet-witch-scene-a112710#gs.earxyp GUARDIANS OF THE GALAXY Was Supposed to Have The Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch Scene]</ref>
*An [[List of Deleted Scenes|alternate ending scene]] was shot for ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'', featuring Quicksilver alive, joining the Avengers and wearing a new costume, along with his sister.<ref name="Alternate ending scene">[http://www.empireonline.com/features/joss-whedon-avengers-ultron-secrets/p4 Joss Whedon Reveals 10 ''Avengers: Age of Ultron'' Secrets/HOW THERE WAS A CHANCE QUICKSILVER WASN'T GOING TO DIE]</ref>
*Despite the fact that Aaron Taylor-Johnson signed a multi-picture deal, [[Kevin Feige]] has stated that there are no plans for Quicksilver to appear in future Marvel Studios films.<ref>[https://www.cinemablend.com/new/What-Kevin-Feige-Thinks-Quicksilver-Future-Marvel-71343.html What Kevin Feige Thinks Of Quicksilver's Future At Marvel]</ref>
*[[James Cox]] was a stunt double for [[Aaron Taylor-Johnson]] in the role of Quicksilver.

